<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4780296>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 2. H. wagini sp. nov., (a) habitus; (b) simplified diagram of a transverse section through the sponge body (abbreviations: at, axial styles which basal ends lying in contact with the substratum; sb, bundles of tornotes supporting the ectosome; dm, dermal membrane; pb, bundles which penetrate the dermal membrane forming conule); (c–f) SEM images of spicules; (c) tornote; (c1) details of apices of tornote; (d) style; (d1) details of apices of style; (e) acanthoxea; (f) acanthostrongyle." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4780296/files/figure.png" .

